1
00:00:00,125 --> 00:00:02,127
She’s been coming here for two days now.

2
00:00:02,168 --> 00:00:03,252
You used to be just like her.

3
00:00:03,253 --> 00:00:04,129
I’m Kara.

4
00:00:04,170 --> 00:00:05,004
Allie.

5
00:00:05,046 --> 00:00:06,088
Did you fight?

6
00:00:06,089 --> 00:00:06,965
Worse.

7
00:00:07,006 --> 00:00:10,927
I realized I feel so suffocated in our relationship.

8
00:00:10,969 --> 00:00:12,470
Is that why you came to Siargao?

9
00:00:12,512 --> 00:00:14,847
Just for the short time that I’ve been here,

10
00:00:14,848 --> 00:00:16,141
I realized that

11
00:00:16,182 --> 00:00:17,892
I don't need permission to be myself.

12
00:00:17,934 --> 00:00:18,852
To do what I want.

13
00:00:19,102 --> 00:00:20,562
[JAO] I’m doing all of this

14
00:00:20,603 --> 00:00:21,646
because I love Allie.

15
00:00:21,813 --> 00:00:22,731
I’ll help you,

16
00:00:22,732 --> 00:00:25,775
but please, spare me the details.

17
00:00:26,192 --> 00:00:27,610
What do you mean, as in everything?

18
00:00:27,652 --> 00:00:29,278
He controls everything.

19
00:00:29,279 --> 00:00:32,407
Plans, schedules, what I eat, what I do-

20
00:00:32,449 --> 00:00:33,575
[JAO] Actually, I made a list

21
00:00:33,616 --> 00:00:35,910
of all the possible places Allie might go to.

22
00:00:35,952 --> 00:00:37,369
[KARA] I'm the tour guide, right?

23
00:00:37,370 --> 00:00:38,580
I don’t think she’ll come here.

24
00:00:38,621 --> 00:00:40,165
[KARA] Jao is stubborn.

25
00:00:40,206 --> 00:00:42,459
He thinks Allie’s just playing hard to get.

26
00:00:42,500 --> 00:00:44,502
He won’t stop until he finds her.

27
00:00:44,544 --> 00:00:46,129
I had a hard time throwing him off.

28
00:00:46,171 --> 00:00:47,714
Just make sure, okay?

29
00:00:47,756 --> 00:00:49,632
That you have sound judgment.

30
00:00:50,717 --> 00:00:51,718
Kara!

31
00:00:55,722 --> 00:00:56,514
[JAO] Allie?

32
00:01:00,935 --> 00:01:01,644
Allie?

33
00:01:08,985 --> 00:01:10,987
I’m not Allie. Who are you?

34
00:01:12,989 --> 00:01:15,575
Sorry, Jess. He thinks you’re his ex.

35
00:01:17,702 --> 00:01:19,704
Sorry. I thought you were someone else.

36
00:01:21,247 --> 00:01:22,624
Are you following me?

37
00:01:24,751 --> 00:01:27,003
I was calling you back there by the main road,

38
00:01:27,045 --> 00:01:28,296
you must not have heard me.

39
00:01:31,674 --> 00:01:32,967
Stop pestering me.

40
00:01:33,009 --> 00:01:35,470
We’ve been searching for Allie all day.

41
00:01:39,933 --> 00:01:40,934
Okay, sorry.

42
00:01:42,185 --> 00:01:43,186
I'll go ahead.

43
00:01:50,568 --> 00:01:51,569
Close call.

44
00:01:52,320 --> 00:01:53,321
I know.

45
00:02:09,170 --> 00:02:12,924
Don’t come. Jao’s here!

46
00:02:25,395 --> 00:02:29,899
[AHON BY JL]

47
00:03:49,729 --> 00:03:59,489
[MAN SINGING]

48
00:04:07,664 --> 00:04:08,581
Excuse me, sir.

49
00:04:08,623 --> 00:04:09,832
Can I ask you something?

50
00:04:09,999 --> 00:04:11,542
Have you seen this girl?

51
00:04:11,793 --> 00:04:13,252
I don’t know her, sir.

52
00:04:13,795 --> 00:04:15,128
Look closely.

53
00:04:15,129 --> 00:04:16,797
I don’t know her.

54
00:04:16,798 --> 00:04:18,216
Okay. Thanks.

55
00:04:27,725 --> 00:04:29,519
Excuse me, ma’am.

56
00:04:29,894 --> 00:04:32,021
Have you seen this girl?

57
00:04:32,063 --> 00:04:32,981
No, I haven't.

58
00:04:34,232 --> 00:04:35,525
Okay, thanks.

59
00:04:38,611 --> 00:04:40,530
Jao! Go get some food there.

60
00:04:41,990 --> 00:04:42,865
I’m fine.

61
00:04:44,701 --> 00:04:46,536
Is there really no other boat available?

62
00:04:46,911 --> 00:04:48,621
No. It’s peak season.

63
00:04:49,038 --> 00:04:50,123
What about that?

64
00:04:50,957 --> 00:04:52,583
That one’s broken.

65
00:04:54,293 --> 00:04:55,628
Is there really no other way we can go someplace else?

66
00:04:55,670 --> 00:04:58,047
Maybe we can rent a private boat.

67
00:04:58,589 --> 00:05:00,133
Well, I can’t leave.

68
00:05:00,174 --> 00:05:01,634
I have a commitment here.

69
00:05:07,515 --> 00:05:09,350
You just won’t quit, huh?

70
00:05:11,519 --> 00:05:12,937
I don’t give up easily.

71
00:05:13,980 --> 00:05:16,816
It's one of the qualities Allie liked about me.

72
00:05:17,942 --> 00:05:19,235
That's why she said yes to me.

73
00:05:19,819 --> 00:05:21,654
Before...

74
00:05:22,697 --> 00:05:25,116
I was so focused on schooling. Plus, I was an introvert.

75
00:05:25,241 --> 00:05:27,118
Allie was the total opposite.

76
00:05:28,911 --> 00:05:31,205
Rich kid, life of the party.

77
00:05:31,414 --> 00:05:33,207
An extrovert, basically.

78
00:05:34,000 --> 00:05:36,543
But when we got together, I really stepped up.

79
00:05:36,544 --> 00:05:38,546
I picked her up and dropped her off every day.

80
00:05:38,588 --> 00:05:39,756
I always check on her.

81
00:05:40,089 --> 00:05:41,632
I would ask her if she has already eaten.

82
00:05:41,674 --> 00:05:43,134
- You know, every-- Maybe that’s why she left.

83
00:05:43,176 --> 00:05:45,011
You babied her too much.

84
00:05:50,475 --> 00:05:52,393
Wait, enough about me.

85
00:05:53,144 --> 00:05:54,437
Why are you here?

86
00:05:54,479 --> 00:05:56,272
What? Leave me out of it.

87
00:05:56,314 --> 00:05:58,316
Why? You're the only one who can ask questions?

88
00:05:59,776 --> 00:06:02,195
I’m just curious because, you know…

89
00:06:02,236 --> 00:06:04,947
How could someone who has a perfect life in the city

90
00:06:05,490 --> 00:06:07,408
decide to move to the island?

91
00:06:08,868 --> 00:06:10,244
You don’t need to know that.

92
00:06:12,997 --> 00:06:13,748
Come on.

93
00:06:20,713 --> 00:06:22,381
Okay. Well…

94
00:06:23,216 --> 00:06:26,010
Here in Siargao, I’m not bound by

95
00:06:26,052 --> 00:06:28,304
other people’s expectations.

96
00:06:29,472 --> 00:06:32,391
I can be myself. I’m not pressured.

97
00:06:32,642 --> 00:06:36,062
Life is slower here, which is really, really nice.

98
00:06:36,729 --> 00:06:38,815
And moving here

99
00:06:39,190 --> 00:06:40,858
made me learn how to stand on my own.

100
00:06:42,902 --> 00:06:44,111
That’s how it is.

101
00:06:44,112 --> 00:06:46,154
You need to leave the place you came from

102
00:06:46,155 --> 00:06:48,157
to learn how to stand on your own.

103
00:06:49,408 --> 00:06:51,744
Who knows? Maybe that's what Allie needs.

104
00:06:56,249 --> 00:06:58,084
I’m not leaving here without her.

105
00:07:08,928 --> 00:07:09,929
A fruit, of course.

106
00:07:11,722 --> 00:07:12,807
Vegan...

107
00:07:13,266 --> 00:07:14,308
Are you good with this?

108
00:07:14,392 --> 00:07:15,393
Thanks.

109
00:07:16,727 --> 00:07:17,979
Anything you want?

110
00:07:19,522 --> 00:07:21,524
Every time I wanted to do something,

111
00:07:21,941 --> 00:07:23,067
he’d just brush it off.

112
00:07:23,109 --> 00:07:26,988
Or he’d make up an excuse…

113
00:07:27,029 --> 00:07:28,155
just to stay in control.

114
00:07:28,156 --> 00:07:29,739
He always had to be in control.

115
00:07:29,740 --> 00:07:31,742
What about what I want?

116
00:07:33,578 --> 00:07:34,871
You can try...

117
00:07:36,205 --> 00:07:37,206
mussels…

118
00:07:38,291 --> 00:07:40,418
and vegetables.

119
00:07:40,793 --> 00:07:41,711
Here.

120
00:07:42,378 --> 00:07:43,254
Is that okay?

121
00:07:55,600 --> 00:07:56,559
Where are you going?

122
00:07:57,310 --> 00:07:59,145
I'm going to ask around over there.

123
00:08:11,574 --> 00:08:14,035
[KARA] Allie, can you…

124
00:08:14,076 --> 00:08:15,203
[ALLIE] I’m leaving tomorrow.

125
00:08:15,244 --> 00:08:16,913
I need to lie low a bit. Let’s meet.

126
00:08:25,880 --> 00:08:27,965
You better sing later.

127
00:08:28,341 --> 00:08:29,341
[WOMAN LAUGHS]

128
00:08:29,342 --> 00:08:31,677
- Come on, hurry. - Brother, need help?

129
00:08:31,719 --> 00:08:33,094
- Let’s get this started. - Almost ready.

130
00:08:33,095 --> 00:08:34,889
It just needs stronger fire.

131
00:08:35,389 --> 00:08:38,225
By the way, are you settling in just fine?

132
00:08:38,226 --> 00:08:40,102
If you need anything, just let me know.

133
00:08:40,144 --> 00:08:42,146
No worries. I’m good, brother.

134
00:08:42,188 --> 00:08:43,564
Your hotel is amazing.

135
00:08:45,775 --> 00:08:47,777
Okay, so what do we have here?

136
00:08:47,818 --> 00:08:49,528
Cooking barbecue…

137
00:08:56,202 --> 00:08:57,245
Oh! Perfect.

138
00:08:57,286 --> 00:08:59,664
[BACKGROUND CHATTER]

139
00:08:59,705 --> 00:09:01,873
Pineapple juice for pork?

140
00:09:01,874 --> 00:09:02,625
Yup!

141
00:09:03,292 --> 00:09:06,336
It makes it more tender and it makes the sauce

142
00:09:06,337 --> 00:09:08,422
more savory and sweet.

143
00:09:08,464 --> 00:09:10,216
That’s what we do in our restaurant.

144
00:09:11,217 --> 00:09:12,385
Let me try it, okay?

145
00:09:20,309 --> 00:09:21,310
Okay, I’ll tell you what…

146
00:09:21,352 --> 00:09:24,355
I’ll do one classic and one with pineapple juice.

147
00:09:25,856 --> 00:09:27,691
Okay. We will taste it later.

148
00:09:27,692 --> 00:09:28,859
If it’s bad,

149
00:09:28,901 --> 00:09:31,279
you will eat everything and pay for it all.

150
00:09:31,320 --> 00:09:31,946
Deal?

151
00:09:32,405 --> 00:09:34,407
Game. But if it’s good, you owe me soju, okay?

152
00:09:34,699 --> 00:09:35,908
- Deal - Good evening.

153
00:09:37,368 --> 00:09:38,369
Jao!

154
00:09:38,619 --> 00:09:40,329
This is Quinito,

155
00:09:40,788 --> 00:09:42,039
the best chef in Manila.

156
00:09:42,081 --> 00:09:43,249
And this is Jao.

157
00:09:43,291 --> 00:09:44,333
- Hi. Jao. - ‘Sup, brother?

158
00:09:44,375 --> 00:09:45,710
- Nice to meet you. - Nice to meet you.

159
00:09:45,835 --> 00:09:46,836
Come on, join us.

160
00:09:47,253 --> 00:09:48,336
- Join us. - Come on, join.

161
00:09:48,337 --> 00:09:49,130
Karaoke night.

162
00:09:49,171 --> 00:09:50,672
No, I’ll pass.

163
00:09:50,673 --> 00:09:52,382
I need to rest. I had a long day.

164
00:09:52,383 --> 00:09:53,175
You guys enjoy.

165
00:09:54,218 --> 00:09:55,261
Oh.

166
00:09:55,803 --> 00:09:57,388
- Too bad. - [ARIEL] That's mama's favorite song!

167
00:09:57,471 --> 00:09:58,973
Okay!

168
00:09:59,015 --> 00:10:00,641
[SIARGAONON] Good evening to you all,

169
00:10:00,683 --> 00:10:01,766
my Katig people!

170
00:10:01,767 --> 00:10:02,601
[CROWD CHEERING]

171
00:10:02,643 --> 00:10:04,186
This song is for you.

172
00:10:04,228 --> 00:10:05,229
Let’s go!

173
00:10:05,271 --> 00:10:05,938
[PEARL CLEARS THROAT]

174
00:10:05,980 --> 00:10:06,772
Go, Miss Pearl!

175
00:10:06,772 --> 00:10:07,690
[PEARL LAUGHING]

176
00:10:09,984 --> 00:10:11,986
[PANGARAP NA BITUIN BY SHARON CUNETA]

177
00:10:12,320 --> 00:10:13,362
[PEARL CLEARS THROAT]

178
00:10:13,988 --> 00:10:15,114
[ARIEL CHUCKLING]

179
00:10:16,240 --> 00:10:22,496
In which corner of the sky will I find

180
00:10:22,955 --> 00:10:25,916
The luck I have never felt.

181
00:10:26,250 --> 00:10:29,545
I have only seen in my dreams.

182
00:10:30,046 --> 00:10:36,551
A glance at the heavens and a genuine smile

183
00:10:36,552 --> 00:10:39,387
Stars will shine

184
00:10:39,388 --> 00:10:44,810
Guiding me to the right path...

185
00:10:44,852 --> 00:10:45,811
Everybody!

186
00:10:45,812 --> 00:10:49,731
Little by little, I will reach

187
00:10:49,732 --> 00:10:52,777
The heavens and the stars

188
00:10:53,402 --> 00:10:59,158
Little by little, my future will shine

189
00:10:59,200 --> 00:11:02,369
I’m holding on

190
00:11:02,370 --> 00:11:06,415
to courage

191
00:11:06,540 --> 00:11:11,003
Tomorrow, when I wake

192
00:11:11,045 --> 00:11:15,674
My dream star will be with me.

193
00:11:15,716 --> 00:11:16,800
There you go!

194
00:11:16,801 --> 00:11:19,720
[CROWD CHEERING]

195
00:11:19,887 --> 00:11:20,971
- Next! - Amazing!

196
00:11:21,013 --> 00:11:22,389
Who’s next?

197
00:11:22,390 --> 00:11:23,391
Han Bin oppa.

198
00:11:23,432 --> 00:11:25,517
- Han Bin oppa! - Han Bin oppa!

199
00:11:25,518 --> 00:11:26,394
- Me? - Yes.

200
00:11:26,435 --> 00:11:27,727
Yes, please sing for us.

201
00:11:27,728 --> 00:11:29,688
[HAN BIN] Okay. Let’s go.

202
00:11:30,064 --> 00:11:31,606
- Han Bin oppa! - Han Bin oppa!

203
00:11:31,607 --> 00:11:33,609
Wow!

204
00:11:33,651 --> 00:11:34,819
[HAN BIN CLEARS THROAT]

205
00:11:35,736 --> 00:11:37,404
[AKIN KA NA LANG BY THE ITCHYWORMS]

206
00:11:37,405 --> 00:11:40,825
[CROWD CHEERING]

207
00:11:40,908 --> 00:11:41,909
[QUINITO] Go, brother!

208
00:11:50,835 --> 00:11:53,796
Don’t believe him

209
00:11:53,838 --> 00:11:57,091
He doesn’t really love you

210
00:11:58,467 --> 00:12:01,220
Your life would be a waste

211
00:12:01,262 --> 00:12:03,431
- If you go with him... - Pearl.

212
00:12:03,472 --> 00:12:04,932
You sing really well.

213
00:12:05,433 --> 00:12:07,017
Do you sing?

214
00:12:07,059 --> 00:12:08,102
Not well.

215
00:12:08,144 --> 00:12:09,186
Do you dance?

216
00:12:09,228 --> 00:12:10,479
Are you sure?

217
00:12:12,857 --> 00:12:14,358
Look at you!

218
00:12:14,859 --> 00:12:17,069
Get up on your feet!

219
00:12:17,695 --> 00:12:19,112
You’re doing great!

220
00:12:19,113 --> 00:12:21,657
More! There you go!

221
00:12:21,699 --> 00:12:22,700
[PEARL LAUGHING]

222
00:12:28,164 --> 00:12:31,375
- Just be mine - [PEARL LAUGHING]

223
00:12:32,918 --> 00:12:36,755
There’s no one better than you.

224
00:12:37,089 --> 00:12:40,049
[CROWD CHEERING]

225
00:12:40,050 --> 00:12:41,469
Thank you, guys.

226
00:12:41,510 --> 00:12:44,680
[CROWD CHEERING]

227
00:12:48,642 --> 00:12:49,727
Han Bin oppa!

228
00:12:50,144 --> 00:12:52,021
I didn’t know you had such a good singing voice.

229
00:12:52,062 --> 00:12:53,147
- Thank you. - I’ll upload the video

230
00:12:53,189 --> 00:12:54,815
of your performance on my vlog, okay?

231
00:12:54,857 --> 00:12:55,816
No, no, no, no!

232
00:12:56,442 --> 00:12:57,234
Why?

233
00:12:57,651 --> 00:12:59,153
You’ll have so many fans.

234
00:12:59,737 --> 00:13:00,945
[HAN BIN SIGHS]

235
00:13:00,946 --> 00:13:02,198
Just please don’t.

236
00:13:02,490 --> 00:13:04,950
I’m a private person. Please don’t do that.

237
00:13:04,992 --> 00:13:06,035
Delete the video.

238
00:13:06,076 --> 00:13:07,827
Okay, chill.

239
00:13:07,828 --> 00:13:10,372
But I’ll send it to you first so that you can see it.

240
00:13:10,706 --> 00:13:12,708
And then I’ll delete the video. Here.

241
00:13:15,878 --> 00:13:16,879
Okay.

242
00:13:17,171 --> 00:13:19,256
I’ll just upload Pearl’s singing video.

243
00:13:19,798 --> 00:13:20,799
Thank you.

244
00:13:21,509 --> 00:13:22,426
[KOREAN] Geon-bae? Cheers?

245
00:13:22,427 --> 00:13:24,345
[KOREAN] Geon-bae. Cheers.

246
00:13:41,695 --> 00:13:42,696
[CAROL] What?

247
00:13:43,781 --> 00:13:45,324
Feeling guilty already?

248
00:13:46,075 --> 00:13:47,117
[KARA GROANS]

249
00:13:47,701 --> 00:13:50,120
I shouldn’t have gotten myself involved.

250
00:13:50,871 --> 00:13:54,333
It feels wrong getting Jao’s hopes up again tomorrow.

251
00:13:56,043 --> 00:13:57,294
So what's your plan?

252
00:14:00,464 --> 00:14:02,758
I’m just thinking of Allie.

253
00:14:03,384 --> 00:14:05,511
She really doesn't want to face Jao.

254
00:14:06,971 --> 00:14:09,723
- Sounds complicated! - I know.

255
00:14:10,683 --> 00:14:11,892
Should I talk to her?

256
00:14:12,226 --> 00:14:13,894
We’re meeting tomorrow.

257
00:14:15,771 --> 00:14:19,817
Do what you think is right.

258
00:14:22,653 --> 00:14:24,238
I’ll make some tea.

259
00:14:24,780 --> 00:14:27,074
- Yes? Okay. - Yes, please.

260
00:14:29,535 --> 00:14:30,786
[CAROL SIGHS]

261
00:14:33,789 --> 00:14:35,207
[KARA SIGHS]

262
00:14:43,757 --> 00:14:47,261
[HORN BLARING]

263
00:14:47,595 --> 00:14:48,554
Sir, is it still there?

264
00:14:48,554 --> 00:14:49,388
Yes, ma'am.

265
00:15:02,026 --> 00:15:04,068
It’s Captain Abong, Pilot.

266
00:15:04,069 --> 00:15:05,112
Pilot.

267
00:15:05,529 --> 00:15:06,739
Very good nice!

268
00:15:07,406 --> 00:15:08,407
Here.

269
00:15:09,116 --> 00:15:10,117
Is that okay?

270
00:15:25,841 --> 00:15:26,842
Allie!

271
00:15:31,930 --> 00:15:32,931
Kara!

272
00:15:33,849 --> 00:15:35,225
Oh, my gosh!

273
00:15:39,063 --> 00:15:40,980
Thank you so much for helping me.

274
00:15:40,981 --> 00:15:42,316
Where are you going?

275
00:15:44,151 --> 00:15:45,194
Anywhere.

276
00:15:45,235 --> 00:15:47,446
Far away from Jao.

277
00:15:48,405 --> 00:15:50,741
Are you really set on that already?

278
00:15:51,408 --> 00:15:54,078
I feel like Jao really cares for you a lot.

279
00:15:55,204 --> 00:15:57,373
He seems to really love you, Allie.

280
00:16:00,793 --> 00:16:03,462
What if you just stay?

281
00:16:08,801 --> 00:16:12,346
[HORN BLARING]

282
00:16:33,575 --> 00:16:37,161
[MIKA] Sir, I found this photo on one of Allie's friend’s profiles.

283
00:16:37,162 --> 00:16:38,789
Taken just last month.

284
00:17:05,524 --> 00:17:07,233
[JAO] You were fooling me all along.

285
00:17:07,234 --> 00:17:10,487
All this time, you made me believe you didn't know Allie.

286
00:17:10,529 --> 00:17:13,823
I thought by keeping you away, I was doing the right thing.

287
00:17:13,824 --> 00:17:14,908
I want to talk to her.

288
00:17:14,950 --> 00:17:16,617
Take me to her, Kara, please.

289
00:17:16,618 --> 00:17:17,619
Hello, Kara?

290
00:17:17,661 --> 00:17:18,912
[KARA] Hello, Allie?

291
00:17:18,954 --> 00:17:19,705
[JAO] Allie?

292
00:17:20,247 --> 00:17:21,373
Hello, Allie?

293
00:17:21,874 --> 00:17:24,209
All he was really thinking about was Allie.

294
00:17:24,251 --> 00:17:26,252
I enabled Allie.

295
00:17:26,253 --> 00:17:27,588
You should have stayed out of it.

296
00:17:27,629 --> 00:17:29,256
[KARA] No need to rub it in.

297
00:17:29,381 --> 00:17:30,673
[BOSS] Everything all right on your end?

298
00:17:30,674 --> 00:17:32,968
I’m flying out Thursday, sir.

299
00:17:33,010 --> 00:17:34,052
[BOSS] Keep me posted.

300
00:17:34,094 --> 00:17:35,846
This project is going to be huge!

301
00:17:36,013 --> 00:17:36,764
[PEARL] Oh!

302
00:17:36,765 --> 00:17:37,806
What happened, Pearl?

303
00:17:37,848 --> 00:17:39,140
Nothing, sir.

304
00:17:39,141 --> 00:17:41,143
- Something is in my eye. - Wait, let me see.

305
00:17:42,853 --> 00:17:43,687
Jao!

306
00:17:43,688 --> 00:17:45,731
We’re going to Pacifico. You want to surf?

307
00:17:45,773 --> 00:17:47,816
No, maybe next time. I need to go somewhere.

308
00:17:47,858 --> 00:17:48,525
Too bad.

309
00:17:48,567 --> 00:17:49,902
You’re going on another tour?

310
00:17:51,153 --> 00:17:52,821
Actually, I found her, Mr. Han.

311
00:17:52,988 --> 00:17:54,031
I found Allie.
